          <div class="blog-recipe-block-ingredients grid__item medium-up--one-half">
          <h3 class="recipe-recipe-block-header underline">Ingredients</h3>
          <ul>
          <li>¼ cup <a href="/collections/plant-milks/products/unsweetened-milked-cashews">Elmhurst Unsweetened Milked Cashews™</a></li>
          <li>1 cup Mango, frozen &amp; sliced</li>
          <li>1 Banana, frozen &amp; sliced</li>
          </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="blog-recipe-block-instructions grid__item medium-up--one-half">
          <h3 class="recipe-recipe-block-header underline">Preparation</h3>
          <ol>
          <li>Add the frozen fruit to a blender or food processor and just enough of the cashew milk for the blades to run. Start with a little at a time and add more as needed.</li>
          <li>This will be thicker than a smoothie, so you may need to stop your blender and scrape down the sides a few times to get everything smooth. Blend until well combined.</li>
          <li>The consistency should be about that of soft-serve or custard and when you tip your blender pitcher back and forth it should mostly stay put.</li>
          <li>Enjoy as is, or pop in the freezer for 15 minutes before serving for a firmer nice cream!</li>
          </ol>
